 Z世代更喜欢在社交媒体上观看影响者而不是电影和电视，研究节目https://www.nme.com/news/gen-z-prefer-watching-influencers-on-social-media-to-film-and-pilm-and-wilm-and-tv-study-shows-3849177？ source = rss＆utm_medium = rss＆utm_campaign = gen-z-z-prefer-tofter-tofter-tofluencer-inflearcer-in-social-media-to-to-to-to-to-to-to-to-tv-study-showsAneesa Ahmed Tue, 25 Mar 2025 20:20:36 +0000 Film NewsNewsTV NewsEntertainmentTV https://www.nme.com/?p=3849177 <p><img width="2000" height="1240" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="社交媒体图标应用。信用-Jonathan Raa/Nurphoto通过Getty Images" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-400x248.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-800x496.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-696x432.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-1392x863.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-1068x662.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>这一代人的时间也比普通人看电视和电影的时间少26％</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gen-z-prefer-watching-influencers-on-social-media-to-film-and-tv-study-shows-3849177">Z世代更喜欢在社交媒体上观看影响者而不是电影和电视，研究节目</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1240" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="社交媒体图标应用。信用-Jonathan Raa/Nurphoto通过Getty Images" decoding="async" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-400x248.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-800x496.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-696x432.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-1392x863.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Social-media-icon-applications.-Credit-Jonathan-Raa_NurPhoto-via-Getty-Images-1068x662.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Z世代更喜欢在社交媒体上观看有影响力的人和创作者驱动的，而不是电影和电视等大型预算<a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/entertainment">娱乐</a>。</p><p>根据调查，ZS一代和43％的千禧一代中有56％的人发现社交媒体内容“比传统的电视节目和电影更相关”，其中一半说他们在电影和电视上对社交媒体人物的个人联系更强。</p><p> <a href="https://www2.deloitte.com/us/en/insights/industry/technology/digital-media-trends-consumption-habits-survey/2025.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">德勤（Deloitte）进行的</a>数字媒体趋势调查向消费者询问了他们的媒体消费习惯。它还评估了他们花费了多少时间消耗不同形式的媒体，并发现Z世代花费的时间多54％，或大约50分钟，而不是每天在社交平台上的平均消费者。这一代人的时间还要少26％，或者每天少44分钟，而不是看电视和电影的普通人。</p><p>德勤有限责任公司副主席中国维德纳（China Widener）告诉<a href="https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/business/business-news/deloitte-gen-z-creator-content-streaming-price-1236171227/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">好莱坞记者</a>：“想想当今，传统媒体和社交媒体之间存在的人们的注意力和时间的战争。因此，当您只是在他们花费时间的情况下考虑这两种服务类型时，您只是在使用这两种服务的情况下？ </p><figure id="attachment_3849189" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3849189" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3849189" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Various-media-libraries-and-streaming-services-on-a-TV.-Credit-Bernd-Weisbrod_picture-alliance-via-Getty-Image-min.jpg" alt="电视上的各种媒体库和流媒体服务。信用-BerndWeißbrod/图片联盟通过Getty" width="2000" height="1240" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Various-media-libraries-and-streaming-services-on-a-TV.-Credit-Bernd-Weisbrod_picture-alliance-via-Getty-Image-min.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Various-media-libraries-and-streaming-services-on-a-TV.-Credit-Bernd-Weisbrod_picture-alliance-via-Getty-Image-min-400x248.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Various-media-libraries-and-streaming-services-on-a-TV.-Credit-Bernd-Weisbrod_picture-alliance-via-Getty-Image-min-800x496.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Various-media-libraries-and-streaming-services-on-a-TV.-Credit-Bernd-Weisbrod_picture-alliance-via-Getty-Image-min-696x432.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Various-media-libraries-and-streaming-services-on-a-TV.-Credit-Bernd-Weisbrod_picture-alliance-via-Getty-Image-min-1392x863.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/Various-media-libraries-and-streaming-services-on-a-TV.-Credit-Bernd-Weisbrod_picture-alliance-via-Getty-Image-min-1068x662.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3849189" class="wp-caption-text">电视上的各种媒体库和流媒体服务。信用 - 通过Getty的BerndWeißbrod/图片联盟</figcaption></figure><p>根据Deloitte的调查，朝着社交媒体人格驱动的内容如此受欢迎的另一个引起的因素是与他们的“个人联系”。某些创作者的粉丝可能会与他们建立副社会关系，从而使参与度保持较高。</p><p>去年，一项研究发现， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/smartphone-now-most-used-screen-for-watching-new-video-content-3775590">智能手机现在是电视前观看新视频内容的“最常用屏幕”</a> 。</p><p>使用Hub Entertainment Research分析的数据的一份<a href="https://variety.com/vip/youtube-tiktok-eroding-viewing-time-spent-streaming-tv-movies-1236069015/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><i>特别</i></a>报告表明，手机屏幕已成为观看视频的首次选择屏幕，在连接电视之前，一个百分点。</p><p>例如，Tiktok用户观看视频内容的平均小时数已从2022年的2.12增加到2024年的2.48，而Instagram， <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/facebook">Facebook</a>和YouTube也证明了类似的增加。</p><p> 2024年的<em>综艺</em>报道强调，电视节目和电影现在占13-24岁的屏幕时间的32％，而35岁以上的观众则为59％。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gen-z-prefer-watching-influencers-on-social-media-to-film-and-tv-study-shows-3849177">Z世代更喜欢在社交媒体上观看影响者而不是电影和电视，研究节目</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
